f\in L^\infty[0,1]
M_f: L^2[0,1]\to L^2[0,1]
M_f(g)(x) = f(x)g(x)
M_f
\|M_f\| = \|f\|_\infty
M_f
g_1,g_2\in L^2[0,1]
\lambda\in\mathbb{R}
 M_f(g_1 + \lambda g_2)(x) = f(x)(g_1(x) + \lambda g_2(x)) = f(x)g_1(x) + \lambda f(x)g_2(x) = M_f(g_1)(x) + \lambda M_f(g_2)(x).
f\in L^\infty
N\in \mathbb{R}
|f(x)| \leq N
\|f\|_\infty = N \lt \infty
M_f
